author: Danny Davis
title: Giddings leaves opponents trying to keep up with Joneses
text:
Giddings senior Kyle Jones admits football fuels a “24/7” conversation inside his home every fall.
There’s always film to break down or plays to scratch out as they distract Jones, a quarterback, from his homework. The dinner table provides a setting for dissecting opponents, and these aren’t one-way conversations, since Kyle’s father, Chris, is in his fifth year as the Buffaloes’ head coach.
